From Grinch Subject Re Limiting Govt was Re Employment was Re Why not In article Steve Hendricks In article Grinch writes Steve you're the one who suggested that a failed government should be an ideal proving ground I never felt that way in the first Quite the contrary I think a better proving ground would be someplace that already had a governemnt that would prevent outright acts of agression yet had a strong spirit of individualism and Someplace Texas Grinch And while Texas taxpayers might willingly eliminate tax support for UT and TAMU I'm not sure they'd support gutting the football Football can pay for Then there's the impact on Ross Perot's fortune of eliminating the various state supported programs where he's made his Why He's already made Sure nodoby else will be able to bilk the public in the same specific ways but why should he or I care All in all Texas doesn't seem to be a very likely place for libertarianism to take More likely than most When I was there the most important state issue was whether to have a state income tax or instead legalize a popular vice for fund raising and vice won a decisive victory jsh Grinch Now that he's safely dead I expect David Koresh to become the hero of popular folk ballads and the ATF to be generally equated with Santa Anna